page.title: 09SYCHAMPTON
page.content: Sychampton is built on a gentle slope surrounded by farmland. It has open views. There are 22 houses in the hamlet of Sychampton. All of them are set well back from the narrow, quiet, country lane in large pretty gardens with ponds, flower-beds and streams. The houses were all large and looked very expensive because they had big extensions and were well maintained. Most of them are old, some of them more than 400 years old but a few are modern. Nearly all of the old ones have been modernised and extended. Many were constructed of red brick some of which had been painted over and some where half timbered. The houses were all detatched. Some were far away from other houses but others were close together. Nearly all of the houses had double garages.
